Peru Bank Lending Rose 20 Percent in April From Year Ago

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-05-23T17:25:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/peru-bank-lending-rose-20-percent-in-april-from-year-ago.html
Peru’s outstanding bank loans rose 20
percent in April from a year earlier as companies and households
demanded more credit, the Andean country’s banking association
Asbanc said.  Outstanding loans totaled 117 billion soles ($42.4 billion)
through April 30,  Asbanc  said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
